A good start, but title makes it sound like the whole universe of shares is covered instead of just 13 issuers.  What you can buy:

&amp;#x200B;

&gt;In addition to Shopify, fractional shares are being offered in Royal Bank of Canada, Toronto Dominion Bank, Canadian National Railway Co., Apple Inc., Amazon.com, Inc., Google LLC, Microsoft Corp., Netflix, Inc., Tesla, Inc., Airbnb, Inc., Coinbase Global Inc., and Nvidia Corp.

rekt since feb.

&amp;#x200B;

was better only buying Microsoft or facebook

I have MSFT and keep being tempted to add more. Perhaps it'll never be cheap, but I have decades until I retire and keen to build a stake. So I would consider averaging up as a result.

&amp;#x200B;

I probably wouldn't buy into say, Disney, because I don't own any shares to average up from and it likewise is a fine company that is very expensive.

&amp;#x200B;

I guess though if I truly believed the stock was overvalued, I'd probably sell it. I'm tempted by £PETS because it seems expensive. If MSFT went to $400 tomorrow, I'm taking that profit and putting it elsewhere. If it's "expensive" but I have faith in the company, I'll consider buying, if it's "overpriced" I won't, and if I hold, I'll sell. 

&amp;#x200B;

I have a list of companies I am planning to focus on in any crash, MSFT among them (and I'd love to pick up Disney at like $140).
